childNodes.textContent: Sprig has been a critical tool in helping teams get more efficient with what and who we prioritize building and iterating for.
Sprig is an integral part of our Product Discovery toolkit. And their customer support team is best-in-class!
By studying customers with Sprig, we’re able to remove the risk around business decisions and new features.
Explore Sprig’s all-in-one product experience platform
Choose the plan that’s right for you

Monthly Tracked Users (MTUs) are unique visitors that have their events sent to Sprig, powering our advanced study targeting. To estimate how many MTUs you'll need, you can use your monthly active user (MAU) count from your analytics tool.
Customize the color and placement of your Web studies.
Completely customize your study design to match the look and feel of your product.
Remove the Sprig footer and add your own logo to your studies.
Sprig is certified in SOC 2 Type II, GDPR, CCPA, and EU/Swiss-U.S. Data Privacy Framework.
Automatically request legal consent from your users within a Sprig study.
Source integrations send user targeting data from external platforms into Sprig.
Includes Javascript, Segment Classic/Web, Google Tag Manager, Optimizely, LaunchDarkly, Census, and RudderStack
Includes Javascript, Segment Classic/Web, Google Tag Manager, Optimizely, LaunchDarkly, Census, and RudderStack
Includes Javascript, Segment Classic/Web, Google Tag Manager, Optimizely, LaunchDarkly, Census, RudderStack, iOS, Android, React Native, Segment Mobile, and Data Import API
Destination integrations send Sprig study data to external platforms.
Includes Mixpanel, Amplitude, Segment Stream, Slack, and User Interviews
Includes Mixpanel, Amplitude, Segment Stream, Slack, and User Interviews
Includes Mixpanel, Amplitude, Segment Stream, Slack, User Interviews, Data Export API, Webhooks, and Zapier
What is an MTU (monthly tracked user)?
Monthly Tracked Users (MTUs) are unique visitors that have their events sent to Sprig. MTUs are what powers Sprig’s advanced study targeting capabilities.
How can I estimate how many MTUs I need?
To approximate how many MTUs you'll need in your Sprig plan, you can use your monthly active user (MAU) count from your product analytics tool as a starting point.
What resources are available to help optimize my use of Sprig?
to help you make the most of the platform . Enterprise customers also receive 1:1 onboarding and customer success support.
How is a MTU (monthly tracked users) different from a page view?

A Monthly Tracked User (MTU) is a unique visitor that has their events sent to Sprig, while a page view is on average, 1 MTU is equal to 1,200 annual page views. When comparing platforms, note that MTU-based pricing often results in a more affordable price point than page view-based pricing.
